What are the parties doing to make it more affordable to start and raise families? Young people want to know, and Generation Squeeze has some answers!

Check out our recent platform analysis (link below) for a detailed breakdown of the parties' stances on all things family policy. We've scored the parties on 12 key criteria from our evidence backed solutions framework for families. From #ChildCare to #ParentalLeave benefits, to giving parents more flexibility to have more time with family.

Our mission this #elxn44 is to ensure you can vote informed on the issues that matter. Check out our Voter's Guide on Family Affordability.

ad_creative_bodies:
#housing is a major issue this #elxn44. So, how close do the party platforms get us to restoring affordability for all? Gen Squeeze dug into each platform and analyzed the parties' promises against our evidence-based solutions frameworks. 

The punchline? No party is proposing enough to restore housing affordability for all. 

There are some good proposals from each party, with some aligning more with the evidence than others. But at the end of the day, each party faces a key challenge in their platforms:

None of the parties propose to restore affordability for all by prioritizing policy changes that would help home prices to stall so that earnings have a chance to catch up.

No matter who wins this election, there's plenty of work we need to do to push for #AffordabilityForAll in Canada.

Want to read how we got these scores? Check out our full analysis at the link below #GenFairnessNow👇 👇👇

https://www.gensqueeze.ca/2021-housing-analysis
